98
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:59,419
[SPEAKER_00] So I think that this is where the fund also can be very helpful.

99
00:11:59,419 --> 00:12:07,980
[SPEAKER_00] So we can have fiscal policy that is prudent in terms of raising revenues, closing tax loopholes,

100
00:12:07,980 --> 00:12:11,980
[SPEAKER_00] prudent in terms of improving the quality of spending.

101
00:12:13,259 --> 00:12:17,100
[SPEAKER_00] Second priority, boost growth potential.

102
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:19,899
[SPEAKER_00] We have done a very interesting study.

103
00:12:19,899 --> 00:12:22,779
[SPEAKER_00] I recommend to everybody here take a look.

104
00:12:22,779 --> 00:12:27,659
[SPEAKER_00] It shows that this potential is quite significant.

105
00:12:27,659 --> 00:12:28,299
[SPEAKER_00] Thank you.

106
00:12:28,299 --> 00:12:35,419
[SPEAKER_00] For the first question, domestic reforms across the CC, let me say it simply.

107
00:12:35,419 --> 00:12:44,539
