119
00:14:04,539 --> 00:14:16,940
[SPEAKER_00] are the equivalent of 44% tariffs for goods and 110% tariffs for services.

120
00:14:18,139 --> 00:14:23,659
[SPEAKER_00] Obviously, this is in our hands to solve.

121
00:14:23,659 --> 00:14:32,940
[SPEAKER_00] And I know that Valdis gets up in the morning, goes to bed thinking about it, Boris,

122
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:41,580
[SPEAKER_00] and working on it much harder than managing the exit of the UK from the European Union.

123
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:57,500
[SPEAKER_00] I, as a European, I see 2025 as a decisive year for the European Union and for the world.

124
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:05,259
[SPEAKER_00] Europe has a tremendous opportunity and responsibility to lead.

125
00:15:06,059 --> 00:15:14,220
[SPEAKER_00] Europe is fantastic as a place that operates on the basis of rules,

126
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:23,899
[SPEAKER_00] where there is respect for each and every one of countries, big and small,

127
00:15:23,899 --> 00:15:34,299
[SPEAKER_00] where there is a social capital built on the basis of our cooperation.

128
00:15:34,299 --> 00:15:43,259
[SPEAKER_00] And I do hope we will see Europe raising to the challenge that is presented to us, the challenge to lead.

129
00:15:43,259 --> 00:15:51,659
